Commerzbank, Salzgitter: German Equity Preview for April 8

-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 
2011-04-08T04:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/commerzbank-salzgitter-german-equity-preview-for-april-8.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  Germany . Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  Germany’s benchmark DAX index declined 0.5 percent to
7,178.78.  Commerzbank AG (CBK)  : Short selling of Germany’s second
largest lender’s shares topped 1 billion euros ($1.43 billion)
in recent weeks, Financial Times Deutschland reported, citing
financial data service Dataexplorers Ltd. The shares fell 4.9
percent to 5.42 euros.  Salzgitter AG (SZG GY): BHP Billiton Ltd. now wants
customers to accept monthly contracts for coking coal delivery,
instead of quarterly, which is likely to mean higher costs for
buyers, the steelmaker’s Chief Executive Heinz Joerg Fuhrmann
said in an interview with Financial Times Deutschland. The
shares lost 1 percent to 57.75 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in  Frankfurt  at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 